# Core Rules

## Rule 1 — Understand Before Coding

Never write code before understanding the real problem.

## Rule 2 — Modify Before Creating

Do not create a new file, folder, component, or function if the existing one can be safely improved.

## Rule 3 — One Goal Per Session

Every work session has one clear objective.

Finish it, test it, commit it, then move on.

## Rule 4 — Explain Every Change

Before changing code, explain:

- Why?
- What will change?
- Possible side effects?
- Is there a better solution?

